Basenji - a cross-platform media indexing/search tool
http://launchpad.net/basenji


GNU/LINUX/GNOME:
================

Requirements:

	mono (2.4 or later)
	glib-sharp (2.12.9 or later)
	gtk-sharp (2.12.9 or later)
	libgnome-desktop (2.32.0 or later)
	gio-sharp (2.22.2 or later)
	dbus-sharp (0.7.0 or later)
	dbus-sharp-glib (0.7.0 or later)
	mono-cairo (2.4.2.3 or later)
	taglib-sharp (>= 2.0.4.0)
	udisks (1.0.1 or later)

Compile:

	./configure (non-gnome: ./configure --config=RELEASE)
	make
	make install

	NOTE:
	if you get a "GLib.GException: Couldn't recognize the 
	image file format for file 'data/basenji.svg'" runtime error,
	you most likely don't have SVG pixbuf loaders installed 
	(package librsvg2-common in ubuntu).
	

MS Windows:
===========

Requirements:

	.NET 4.0 Framework
	Gtk# for .NET (http://www.go-mono.com/mono-downloads/download.html)
	System.Data.SQLite (http://sqlite.phxsoftware.com/)
	taglib-sharp (https://github.com/mono/taglib-sharp)
	
Compile:

	Open Basenji_win32.sln in Visual Studio 2008.
